<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: JAZZ 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and international 
news services and the nation's press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 New Gig for Taylor: Pianist Billy Taylor has been named artistic director and 
host of a new series of broadcasts to be co-produced by National Public Radio 
and the Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts in Washington. 
</P>
<P>
 The broadcasts, which will be taped in Washington and begin airing on NPR in 
fall, 1995, are dubbed "Billy Taylor's Jazz at the Kennedy Center." The series 
is "designed to acquaint listeners with the rich history and diversity of 
American jazz." 
</P>
