</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEONARD FEATHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *** 1/2 Kitty Margolis, "Evolution," Mad-Kat. From the label that gave us 
Madeline Eastman comes another underrated singer.She cooks in bop 
("Anthropology"), is lyrical on ballads ("Where Do You Start?"), superbly gutty 
on blues (a quasi-hysterical "Please Send Me Someone to Love"). Joe Henderson 
guests on several tunes, among them Wayne Shorter's "Footprints" and Cedar 
Walton's "Firm Roots," for both of which Margolis supplied sensitive lyrics. As 
Jon Hendricks' liner notes point out, Margolis possesses impeccable taste and 
selectivity. (Available from Mad-Kat Records, P.O. Box 420253, San Francisco, 
94142). 
</P>
<P>
 New albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three 
stars (good, recommended), four stars (excellent). LEONARD FEATHER 
