NEW RELEASES / JAZZ; IN BRIEF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ZAN STEWARD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *** 1/2 Don Braden, "Wish List," Criss Cross. The tenor saxophonist, who has 
played with Wynton Marsalis and Tony Williams, is one fine composer and 
arranger.Even if he hadn't hired some of the cream of today's jazz crop -- Tom 
Harrell (trumpet), Benny Green (piano), Steve Turre (trombone) and Christian 
McBride (bass) -- this album of originals and just-so arranged standards and 
jazz classics would still sound superb. A bubbling hold-back rhythm keeps 
"Father Time" popping along, and "Just the Facts" is a firebrand blues. The 
leader's tone -- bright and beaming -- is the first thing you notice about his 
playing, but soon his surging lines demand attention. Harrell's squiggly yet 
driving ideas are always riveting, and Green really opens up here and stretches 
out. New albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), 
three stars (good, recommended), four stars (excellent). ZAN STEWARD 
</P>
