BASEBALL / DAILY REPORT; ANGELS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB NIGHTENGALE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Angel starter John Farrell cleared waivers Thursday and is expected to accept 
an assignment to triple-A Vancouver. "I just want to get back to pitching 
again," he said. . . . Angel outfielder Dwight Smith sang the national anthem 
before Thursday's game, prompting the entire Cub team to bow to him in tribute. 
. . . Angel left fielder Bo Jackson returned to the lineup Thursday after 
leaving Wednesday's game with a cramp in his right calf. . . . Dan O'Brien, 
former Angel vice president, was hired Thursday as director of baseball 
operations for the Arizona Fall League . . . Jackson teased designated hitter 
Chili Davis before the game, reminding Davis that he has one hit fewer than 
Michael Jordan this spring. . . . Rodgers said Greg Myers will probably catch 
Chuck Finley this season, and Chris Turner will catch Mark Langston. The rest 
of the playing time between the catchers, Rodgers said, will be divvied up 
according to merit. BOB NIGHTENGALE 
</P>
