<P>
BASEBALL / DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MAJORS; INDIANS PARK WON'T GO UP IN SMOKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The new Cleveland Indians' ballpark, built in part with a county-wide tax on 
tobacco products, will prohibit smoking in all seating areas.Smoking at Indians 
Park will be limited to six areas that do not have direct views of the playing 
field. 
</P>
<P>
 The Atlanta Braves say they will pay Ron Gant $901,639.20, or 30 days' 
termination pay, rather than trying to pay him none of his $5.5 million 
contract. The Braves released the injured outfielder Tuesday. Gant broke his 
right leg in a dirt bike accident Feb. 3. 
