<P>
PREP TRACK ROUNDUP; EDISON WINS 21ST CONSECUTIVE SUNSET MEET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Edison won its 21st consecutive Sunset League girls' track and field meet with 
a 105 1/2-20 1/2 victory over Ocean View Thursday at Ocean View High. 
</P>
<P>
 The Chargers have not lost a league meet since the 1991 season. 
</P>
<P>
 Marie Philman, Kelly Marshall and Kerry O'Bric were multiple winners for the 
Chargers (3-0, 2-0). Philman won the high jump (5 feet 1), shot put (36-0) and 
discus (129-4). 
</P>
<P>
 Marshall won the 200 meters (26.9), 400 (1:01.0) and was part of the winning 
1,600 relay (4:19) and 400 relay (51.5). O'Bric also won the 300 hurdles 
(50.04) and ran on the 400 relay team. 
</P>
