<HEADLINE>
<P>
FALLING "STAR" SHINES IN VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After nearly falling early in the stretch, favored Dezibelle's Star gathered 
herself and went on to win the $81,200 La Habra Stakes Thursday at Santa Anita. 
</P>
<P>
 Attempting to rally between horses under Gary Stevens, the 3-year-old 
Prospective Star filly was shut off when the hole closed.She got going again, 
though, and was able to beat 5-2 second choice Sophisticatedcielo by a length 
in 1:14 for the about 6 1/2 furlongs on the turf. 
</P>
<P>
 This was the third consecutive victory for the even-money favorite, who is 
owned by Gordon Molitor and trained by Jack Van Berg. 
</P>
<P>
 "I've never seen anything quite like that and I've dang sure never been on one 
that did she what she just did," said Stevens. 
</P>
<P>
 Sophisticatedcielo finished a length in front of Ballerina Gal, then came 
Airistar, Dancing Ovation and Gambling Mistress. BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
