<HEADLINE>
<P>
DOS REMEDIOS NAMED AS COACH OF BURROUGHS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DANA HADDAD, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In a decision that was not popular with Burroughs High football players and a 
13-member search comitteee, the Burbank Unified School District Board of 
Education named Robert dos Remedios as new head football coach Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
 The board, after meeting in closed session, voted 5-0 in favor of a 
recommendation by Burroughs principal Tim Buchanan. 
</P>
<P>
 During the meeting, Burroughs quarterback Scott Boldvich spoke out in support 
of Burroughs assistant Pat Blackburn, the candidate the search committee voted 
7-6 to support. 
</P>
<P>
 "We listen to this coach at least 25 hours a week," Boldvich said. "We bond 
with him. The bond is basically between the players and Blackburn. The players 
should at least get an equal say at who's the next coach." 
</P>
<P>
 Buchanan said he chose Dos Remedios, 27, because he's intelligent, has a lot 
of energy, knows the community and has five years of coaching experience at 
Glendale College. 
</P>
<P>
 The committee however, supported Blackburn, citing a concern that Dos Remedios 
had no head-coaching experience. 
</P>
<P>
 "Neither did Gary Bernardi," said Buchanan of Dos Remedios' predecessor, now 
an assistant at UCLA. 
</P>
<P>
 Dos Remedios, who will become the fifth Burroughs coach in four years, did not 
attend the meeting. Neither did Blackburn, who was contacted at home during the 
closed session. 
</P>
<P>
 "I don't think I want to make a statement at this point," said Blackburn, who 
was recommended by Bernardi.  
</P>
<P>
 "The players have voiced that they are supporting me and I have plenty of 
people in the community supporting me." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA031894-0114 </DOCNO>
