<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; NORTHRIDGE'S BURTON FINISHES 35TH IN NCAA ONE-METER 
SPRINGBOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Freshman Dawn Burton of Cal State Northridge finished 35th in the one-meter 
springboard competition Thursday in the NCAA women's swimming and diving 
championships at Indianapolis. 
</P>
<P>
 Burton finished with 319.90 points in the preliminaries. Vanessa Thelin of 
Brigham Young won the title. Only eight divers qualified for the semifinals and 
finals. 
</P>
<P>
 Burton will compete in the three-meter springboard and 10-meter platform 
events later this week. She is the first Matador diver to qualify for the NCAA 
diving championships since Northridge moved to Division I in 1990. BASEBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Canyons 21, Bakersfield 16 -- First baseman Tommy Nichols and third baseman 
Ted Keister had four hits each to lead a 25-hit attack for the Cougars in a 
Western State Conference game. Catcher David Castillo was three for four with 
five RBIs and shortstop Chris Pfaterhoauer was two for five with four RBIs for 
Canyons. 
</P>
<P>
 Valley 9, Santa Monica 6 -- Ozzie Areu scored the go-ahead run for Valley in 
the 14th inning on sophomore third baseman Vic Seper's two-out double in the 
WSC game. 
</P>
<P>
 Areu (four for five), Seper (four four six), Marlon Hamilton (three for seven) 
and Jamie Zeichick (two for five) led a 16-hit Monarch attack in a WSC game. 
Monarch pitchers Francisco Mere, Doug Melvin and Ryan Messevier (2-0) gave up 
five hits in nine innings of scoreless relief. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura 7, Oxnard 6 -- Jameal Nichol's infield single drove in David Frazier 
with two out in the ninth inning to give the Pirates a WSC victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Frazier had a two-run double to spark a four-run rally in the ninth inning for 
Ventura, which fell behind, 5-0, in the first inning. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference games: 
</P>
<P>
 L.A. City 7, Antelope Valley 4 -- Ryan Branch went two for three and scored 
twice in a losing effort at Antelope Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Al Watson paced L.A. City (11-6) by going three for four with a double and 
triple and drove in three runs. Teammate Ernie Diaz hit solo homers in the 
fifth and ninth innings. 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley is 9-6. 
</P>
<P>
 Mission 3, Moorpark 2 -- Gary Mathews scored the go-ahead run in the 11th 
inning on a sacrifice fly by Jesus Perez to lift Mission (12-10) over Moorpark 
(8-8-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Mission starter Robert Ballester allowed three hits in 11 innings. Ballester 
(4-1) struck out six, walked two and did not allowed an earned run. 
</P>
<P>
 Steve Chavez had two hits for Mission. 
</P>
