<P>
From a Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Santa Ana man and his wife were released Thursday after Orange County 
authorities said they lacked evidence to charge the couple with shooting his 
mother to death on an apartment balcony. 
</P>
<P>
 Santos Alvarez Roque and Maria Bruno Soto, both 24, had been arrested on 
Wednesday on suspicion of homicide.His mother, Valentina Roque, 55, was killed 
Sunday night by what police initially believed was random gunfire. 
</P>
<P>
 In an interview after the shooting, a tearful Roque had called for an end to 
gun violence. Police later said his account of the incident conflicted with his 
wife's and with evidence investigators discovered. 
