GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: BURBANK; 4 MEN EXPECTED TO BE CHARGED IN SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHAU LAM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A jilted lover is among four men expected to be charged today in connection 
with the shooting of a Los Angeles man earlier this week, authorities said 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Arrested within hours of the 4 p.m. Wednesday shooting were Robert Young, 27, 
and Marcelo Flores, 26, both of Burbank; John Matthews Jr., 30, of Northridge, 
and Malcolm Alarca, 22, of Sunland. 
</P>
<P>
 The 27-year-old victim is in fair condition. Police did not identify the 
victim. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said the dispute centered on an unnamed woman who stopped dating Young 
in order to date the victim. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim was shot several times at close range as he entered his car parked 
in the 3200 block of San Fernando Boulevard, authorities said. No words were 
exchanged in the incident and police refused to name the triggerman. The weapon 
used in the shooting has not been recovered. CHAU LAM 
