<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: NORWALK; TRIAL SET FOR 
EX-TV HOST ACCUSED OF MURDER PLOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An April 27 trial date was set Thursday for a former cable TV talk show host 
and his father, who allegedly tried to hire a hit man to kill a girl whose 
testimony eventually helped convict the younger man of rape.  
</P>
<P>
 Tito David Valdez Jr., 23, was sentenced on March 4 to 14 years in prison for 
rape and child molestation. 
</P>
<P>
 According to the 13-year-old girl's testimony during the trial, the younger 
Valdez picked her up at her home around midnight on April 28, 1993, to 
interview her for a job on his program, "Hollywood Haze." Valdez claimed it was 
the only time he could be free to interview her. He then took her to his Downey 
home and raped her. 
</P>
<P>
 Valdez and his father will be tried for solicitation to commit murder and 
conspiracy to commit murder. They allegedly paid an undercover Downey police 
officer to shoot the girl so she could not testify in the rape trial. 
</P>
</TEXT>
