<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; IT'S IN THE CARDS: PSYCHICS TO GATHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB ELSTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For those who did not know already, the Spring Psychic Fair is being held here 
on March 26 and 27.  
</P>
<P>
 According to the fair's organizer, veteran astrologer Kathleen Scott, people 
who specialize in handwriting analysis, past-life readings, palm readings and 
various psychic paraphernalia will congregate at the Hyatt Newporter for the 
two-day fair. 
</P>
<P>
 Scott encourages skeptics as well as believers to attend, "mostly for the fun 
of it and (out of) plain curiosity."  
</P>
<P>
 Scott does astrology readings using a 100-year calendar that tells her where 
the planets were positioned at the precise moment of a subject's birth. From 
that information, she interprets how the planets will influence a person's 
personality, and claims to have predicted pregnancies and job promotions. 
</P>
<P>
 "It is a lot of fun," she said. 
</P>
<P>
 There will be vendors selling incense, candles and jewelry as well as readers 
of palms, Tarot cards and astrology charts. 
</P>
<P>
 Admission is free but readings and such will cost. The Hyatt Newporter is at 
1107 Jamboree Road in Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 645-9900. BOB ELSTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
