</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Senior Housing Sale: Host Marriott Corp. said that it has agreed to sell 14 
senior living facilities, including a seven-story facility in Laguna Hills, to 
Health and Rehabilitation Properties Trust of Newton, Mass. The company is 
selling the Marriott Villa Valencia, a senior citizens home with 345 apartments 
and a 59-bed health center at 24552 Paseo de Valencia.The facilities are 
currently leased to Marriott International Inc., which will continue to operate 
them under long-term leases so there will be no change in day-to-day 
operations, the company said. Besides Laguna, the senior living facilities are 
located in Ft. Myers, Deerfield Park, Port St. Lucie, Palm Harbor and Boca 
Raton, Fla.; Silver Spring, Md.; Arlington Heights, Ill.; Arlington, Va.; 
Houston, and Scottsdale and Sun City, Ariz. The transaction still must be 
approved by both companies' boards of directors. 
</P>
