<HEADLINE>
<P>
LAS VEGAS CONVERSIONS PAYING OFF IN BIG SALES AT DEL TACO RESTAURANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Del Taco Inc. said Thursday that it has converted seven former Naugles 
restaurants in Las Vegas into Del Tacos, and seen big sales increases as a 
result. 
</P>
<P>
 The conversion was completed in January, said Paul Hitzelberger, executive 
vice president of the Orange-based chain of Mexican-style fast-food 
restaurants. 
</P>
<P>
 Even as Naugles, the restaurants had sales volumes roughly equal to those in 
Del Taco's core Southern California market. He said that since the change, the 
restaurants saw sales increases ranging from 70% to 180% compared to the same 
period last year. 
</P>
<P>
 "There was a complete exterior remodel that reflects much of what the logo 
signifies, which is a fun, festive celebration, the start of a new day at Del 
Taco with the sun coming up over the mountain," Hitzelberger said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
